history.content:
Its really hard to answer those types of likelihood questions. You can look at previous years and try to make a conclusion from that, but even then you cannot be sure with your prediction. 

I would say that it is not likely that the course will be expanded this late in the semester and #45 on the wait list does not seem high enough to get off the list anytime soon.

I would say that it is not likely that the course will be expanded this late in the semester and #45 on the wait list does not seem close enough to get off the list anytime soon.

I'm currently number 40 on the wait list and I sent an email to fa17@eecs70.org asking a similar question. Professor Rao responded by saying I was likely to get in due to people dropping after the first midterm and some expansion. So all hope is not lost yet! You may want to send an email to them too just to be sure.

At the moment, I am a cs-intended sophomore. I am currently waitlisted for CS70 at position #45. As the second week comes to an end, are my chances based on people dropping and my position moving up? Or is there a chance of the class being expanded to accommodate more?
